    "Furthermore, healthcare workers, like as physicians and nurses, are at a higher risk of transmission resulting from their regular interaction with sick patients (Masirika et al., 2024a).",
    "The Democratic Republic of the Congo is witnessing a significant incidence of illnesses among youth linked to clade Ib.",
    "Most fatalities and more than half of confirmed instances occur in children under the age of five, making children a vulnerable group for Mpox transmission.",
    "Epidemiologists have also identified transmission clusters associated with heterosexual or public sexual contacts (for example, sex workers in Kamituga), which were not popular during the clade II outbreak in 2022 (Katoto et al., 2024; Rivers et al., 2024).",
    "HIV-positive and immunocompromised people are especially vulnerable to infection."
